 double-draft/double-submit guards), store.cljc (MemStore +
 DatomicStore via kotoba-lang/langchain-store's entity field-spec
 map->tx/pull->map/pull-pattern AND its identity-schema/event-log
 helpers, engagement entity tracking the classification ground-truth
 facts, cooperation-readiness flag, conditional subsidy-retention
 fields, and the single actionable :audit-readiness-package filing
 track's actuation state), auditreadinessllm.cljc (mock Compliance
 Advisor), operation.cljc (intake -> advise -> govern -> decide ->
 [request-approval ->] commit/hold StateGraph), phase.cljc (0->3
 rollout, :filing/draft and :filing/submit permanently excluded from
 every phase's :auto set). 39 tests / 121 assertions passing (governor
 contract + store parity + facts + phase + registry), clj-kondo clean
 (0 errors, 0 warnings). Domain reconciled against the pre-existing
 (2026-07-10) blueprint text, which already correctly scoped this
 actor to Board-of-Audit audit-readiness/record-keeping compliance
 (not general Japan market entry) -- no scope pivot was needed, unlike
 cloud-itonami-iso3166-jpn-mof/-moe; the implementation pass instead
 made two framing points explicit (jurisdiction attaches
 automatically by statute, never by application; :filing/draft and
 :filing/submit name the operator's own compliance-package act, never
 a submission the Board of Audit itself receives) -- see
 docs/business-model.md's Domain note for the full reconciliation."}
